{
["TX"] = "{h1:c}{col:ff00e3}Description{/col}{/h1}{h3}{col:ff60e8}An oddity of sorts, Meera is an elven-like girl with--oddly enough--cat ears and a cat tail, all of them the same shade of color as her dark-purple-ish, curly hair. Upon first glance, one would assume she'd be able to hear excellently due to having ears like that, but it is not the case for Meera. She's deaf, so trying to get her attention by talking to her while she's reading something or looking elsewhere will not work. She's also mute, since whenever she opens her mouth to laugh or anything similar, no sound comes from her throat. She mainly seems to communicate either with Sign Language or, more often, a small notebook, the pages within it enchanted to always erase what is written on them whenever Meera runs out of room to write. She's...at least seen to be physically mute and deaf. Mentally...well, who knows? The only time she seems to be able to hear is when she has her hearing aids.\n\nHer eyes are not the same colors due to heterochromia: her left eye is silver with a pink, star-shaped pupil while the other eye is pink with a silver star-shaped pupil. \n\nOn her cheeks are void-colored markings, two on each cheek. She was born with these markings, no one in her family knowing why or how she even had them. HIdden in her hair, barely visible, are two oni horns, both a pearly-pink color, like her mother's horns.\n\nOn her tiny frame, she wears a kimono-styled dress, the sleeves being slightly too long and covering her hands. Often, along with the dress, she's seen carrying around a plush of sorts: either a small teddy bear or a worgen-like plush with a little skull-face. They both appear to be her comfort companions.{/col}{/h3}",
